terns used for parsing Google careers HTML (lines 205-207) could be vulnerable to ReDoS (Regular Expression Denial of Service) with carefully crafted HTML, though risk is mitigated by timeouts.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"informational\",\n      \"file\": \"notify.py\",\n      \"line\": 72,\n      \"description\": \"SMTP credentials retrieved from environment variables. Ensure environment variables are not logged or exposed in error messages. Current implementation appears safe but should add explicit checks.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"riskScore\": 23,\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add HTML entity escaping for Slack messages: use json.dumps() for text blocks or escape special characters (& < > \\\" ') before concatenation\",\n    \"Validate webhook payloads: implement JSON schema validation and sanitize raw ATS data before sending to webhook endpoints\",\n    \"Make Meta GraphQL doc_id configurable: move _META_DOC_ID to configuration and add initialization script to capture it from live site\",\n    \"Implement config schema validation: use a validation library (e.g., pydantic or marshmallow) to validate sources.yaml structure and value constraints\",\n    \"Add input validation for configuration parameters: enforce reasonable limits on max_pages, concurrency, timeouts\",\n    \"Test regex patterns for ReDoS vulnerability: use regex101.com or similar tools to validate patterns, consider adding regex timeout guards\",\n    \"Add centralized secret handling: implement a secrets manager pattern that prevents accidental logging of SMTP_PASS, API tokens\",\n    \"Database: consider enabling foreign keys and integrity constraints: add PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON to store.py initialization\",\n    \"Add rate limiting: implement exponential backoff with jitter already exists, but consider per-domain limits to avoid overwhelming ATS servers\",\n    \"Dependency scanning: regularly scan httpx and PyYAML versions for known vulnerabilities using tools like pip-audit or saf